    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker</strong> to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef </strong>to the dish with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Crush your<strong> garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Slice your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion wedges</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to the dish with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>beef stock mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained black beans </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> to a small bowl with your <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled green chilli</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>slow cooker chipotle beef stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has 15 min left, chop your<strong> potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a large heat-proof bowl covered with<strong> cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 8-10 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and roughly crush with a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-chipotle-beef-stew-with-chilli-pickle-sweet-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>slow cooker chipotle beef stew</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>crushed potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the potatoes with the <strong>quick-pickled</strong> <strong>green chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>pickling liquid</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>chilli pickle potatoes</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
